    "what_description": "Zanthoxylum bungeanum is a deciduous shrub or small tree native to China, belonging to the family Rutaceae. Its botanical characteristics include simple, alternate, and ovate leaves, measuring 5-10 cm in length, with entire margins and 2-4 pairs of lateral veins. The leaves are dark green above and paler below, with a glabrous and slightly leathery texture. The plant produces small, yellow flowers in panicles, 5-10 cm long, with 4-5 petals and a 4-lobed calyx. The fruit is a reddish-brown, globose drupe, 1-2 cm in diameter, containing 1-2 seeds.",
