    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Zanthoxylum bungeanum are exhibited through its antioxidant activity, attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids. This plant also displays antimicrobial properties, which are largely due to the presence of saponins and volatile oils that inhibit the growth of various pathogens. Additionally, Zanthoxylum bungeanum exhibits anti-inflammatory properties, resulting from the activity of its alkaloids and terpenoids that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory mediators. The analgesic properties of this plant are mediated by the presence of lignans and coumarins that interact with pain receptors to reduce pain perception. Furthermore, its antiviral properties are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and terpenoids that inhibit the replication of viral particles.",
