    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Zanthoxylum bungeanum are zanthoxylum alkaloids, particularly zanthoxylin, which exhibit anti-inflammatory and analgesic activities by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory mediators and blocking the action of pain receptors. Flavonoids present in Zanthoxylum bungeanum, such as quercetin and kaempferol, display antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, scavenging free radicals and inhibiting the activity of inflammatory enzymes. Coumarins, like scopoletin and esculetin, in Zanthoxylum bungeanum possess anticoagulant and anti-inflammatory effects, preventing blood clot formation and reducing inflammation by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Phenolic acids, including ferulic and caffeic acids, found in Zanthoxylum bungeanum, exhibit antioxidant and antimicrobial activities, protecting against oxidative stress and inhibiting the growth of microorganisms. These bioactive compounds in Zanthoxylum bungeanum contribute to its traditional use in treating various health conditions, including pain, inflammation, and infection.",
