    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Zanthoxylum bungeanum improperly include inducing nausea, developing allergic reactions, and increasing heart rate due to its bioactive compounds such as flavonoids and alkaloids, which can stimulate the central nervous system and cause adverse reactions when ingested in excessive amounts or without proper preparation. Experiencing nausea is also a common side effect, as the plant's volatile oils can irritate the digestive system and cause stomach discomfort. Furthermore, ingesting Zanthoxylum bungeanum can induce allergic reactions in some individuals, particularly those with pre-existing sensitivities to certain plant compounds. The increased heart rate is a result of the plant's stimulatory effects on the cardiovascular system, which can lead to an increase in blood pressure and other cardiovascular issues. These side effects can be prevented by proper preparation, dosage, and usage of the plant under the guidance of a qualified healthcare professional."
